        <title>About Whyteboard</title>
    </head>
    <body>
       	<p>Whyteboard is a free painting application that can run on Linux, Windows and Mac. It is suited towards creating visual presentations and for overlaying PDF images with annotations.</p>
       	<h3>Program Features</h3>
		<ul id="features">
	        <li>Draw using familiar tools: pen, rectangle, circle, text, arrows</li>
	        <li>Annotate over PDF files</li>
	        <li>Resize, move and rotate shapes you've drawn</li>
	
	        <li>Multiple sheets - draw with an intuitive tab interface</li>
	        <li>Embed an audio/video player onto the canvas</li>
	        <li>Your drawings are recorded and can be replayed</li>
	        <li>Each sheet has a preview thumbnail of itself</li>
	        <li>Note items, similar to "sticky notes"</li>
	        <li>Resize the canvas easily by dragging anywhere outside of its border</li>
	
	        <li>Translated into many languages e.g. Chinese, French, German, Spanish, Italian, Turkish, Portuguese and many more</li>
	        <li>Closed sheets can be re-opened, restoring their drawings and complete undo and drawing history</li>
	    </ul>
        
